==English==

===Etymology===
From {{suffix|absolute|ness|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈab.sə.luːt.nəs/|/ab.səˈluːt.nəs/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈæb.səˌlut.nəs/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|es}}

# {{label|en|obsolete}} The fact of being [[finished]] or [[perfected]]; [[completeness]]. {{defdate|Attested from the mid 16<sup>th</sup> century until the 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}
# The characteristic of being absolute in nature or scope.
#: ''the '''absoluteness''' of his sovereignty,&emsp; the '''absoluteness''' of his convictions''
# Absolute [[authority]], unlimited power; [[absolutism]], [[despotism]]. {{defdate|First attested in the 16<sup>th</sup> century.}}
#* {{RQ:Flr Mntgn Essays}}, II.8:
#*: I know no man that could produce more parts, both naturall and artificiall, fit to preserve his masterie, and to maintaine his '''absolutenesse''', than he doth; yet is hee cleane falne from them like a childe.
# The fact of being without qualifications or conditions; [[certainty]], unconditionality. {{defdate|First attested in the 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}
# Independent [[autonomy]]. {{defdate|First attested in the 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}

